         <div>
            <head>32) <hi rend="bold">d-minor</hi>.</head>
            <p>Tonic C-major = the dominant of F-major; relative (g-minor) to the sub-dominant of
               F-major; use this g-minor, which is at the same time the sub-dominant in d-minor.
               (Cadence!)</p>
            <p>[C<hi rend="superscript">I</hi> (= F<hi rend="superscript">V</hi>), F<hi
               rend="superscript">II</hi> (= d<hi rend="superscript">IV</hi>), d<hi
                  rend="superscript">V<hi rend="superscript">6</hi><hi rend="subscript"
                     >4</hi></hi>, d<hi rend="superscript">V<hi rend="subscript">&#9839;
                        <!-- ♯, music sharp sign--></hi></hi>, | d<hi rend="superscript">I</hi>]</p>
            <p>
               <figure>
                  <notatedMusic place="inline">
                     <!--Link to the image file with description:-->
                     <graphic
                        url="reger_image1.png" height="4em">
                        <desc>Reger example 1</desc>
                     </graphic>
                  </notatedMusic>
               </figure>  
               (phrygisch!) </p>
              
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>33) <hi rend="bold">g-minor</hi>.</head>
            <p>Tonic C-major, which is used, as it is also the chord of the Dorian<ref target="#fn01" type="noteAnchor">*)</ref>
               sixth in g-minor; dominant (D-major) with 7th (2nd inversion) of g-minor.</p>
            <p>[C<hi rend="superscript">I</hi> (= g<hi rend="superscript">IV<hi rend="subscript">3</hi></hi>&#9838;<!-- ♮, music natural sign -->), g<hi rend="superscript"><hi rend="underline"
               n="2">V</hi><hi rend="superscript">7</hi><hi rend="subscript">&#9839;
                  <!-- ♯, music sharp sign--></hi></hi>, g<hi rend="superscript">I</hi>]</p>
         </div>
            <div>
               <figure>
                  <notatedMusic place="inline">
                     <!--Link to the image file with description:-->
                     <graphic
                        url="reger_image2.png" height="10em">
                        <desc>Reger example 2</desc>
                     </graphic>
